programs.title: The Runners’ Strength & Stretch Guide: Glutes and Hip Flexors
programs.requirements: Barbells or Dumbbells, Straps or Band, Knee Pad, Bench, Machines(Optional)

exercises.name: Strength 1: Curtsy Lunges
exercises.note: Details: Perform a lateral lunge while crossing one leg behind the other, akin to a curtsy. Use a strap or band to maintain balance and focus the load on the heel. Note: You only need to step behind your front foot. Crossing far outside your front foot is unnecessary and will lead to uneven hip posture.

exercises.name: Strength 2: Barbell Walking Lunges
exercises.note: Details: Perform walking lunges with a barbell placed behind your neck. Ensure each knee lightly taps the ground to engage the glutes properly. Note: May swap barbell for dumbbells or body weight.

exercises.name: Strength 3: Barbell 90° Squat with Hip Thrust
exercises.note: Detail: Squat to a 90-degree angle, then powerfully, but with control in one motion thrust your hips upward as you rise, tightly flexing your glutes. Note: Aim for 70% of your max repetition weight or above.

exercises.name: Strength 4: Single Leg Hip Thrust on Bench
exercises.note: Details: Perform hip thrusts with one leg, using a bench for support. Keep the thrust controlled, and focus on squeezing the glutes at the top of the movement. Note: Use a bench.

exercises.name: Strength 5: Fire Hydrants
exercises.note: Details: From a tabletop position, lift one leg away from the body, keeping the knee bent. This exercise targets the gluteus medius and minimus for improved lateral stability.

exercises.name: Stretch 1: Kneeling Hip Flexor Stretch
exercises.note: Details: From a tabletop position, lift one leg away from the body, keeping the knee bent. This exercise targets the gluteus medius and minimus for improved lateral stability. Note: Use foam pad or mat to protect knee.
